West Ham manager Sam Allardyce admits it is a worry that his leading goalscorer was forced off the field

‘For me, my big worry is that my leading goalscorer came off with a shoulder problem,’ said Allardyce. ‘I just sincerely hope that damage is not severe and that he can carry on because when you have someone who scores six in six [in the league] you can ill afford to lose him and if we lose him that will be a big blow.

Sakho has been sensational since his £3.5million switch from Metz in the summer, and even though he agreed a four-year, £20,000-a-week deal when he joined, co-owner David Sullivan wants to reward his form with a revised contract.

Allardyce was angered, however, when Sergio Aguero escaped a booking for a stamp on Mark Noble.

