He said: ‘(Noble) was complaining bitterly about it. If you have a look at it you can make your own mind up. For me it’s a very dangerous tackle.’

City boss Manuel Pellegrini claimed his side had chances to win but paid the price for not matching West Ham in the first half.

He said: ‘In the first half we did not play with enough intensity, I thought they would be more tired in the second half and we would be able to move the ball easier, which we did, but in the end we couldn’t take our chances.’

